01/07/2003
TIRANA, Albania -- Foreign ministers and other officials from Balkan countries gathered Monday (30 June) in Tirana to discuss the development of Pan-European Transport Corridor 8, which would link Albania's Adriatic port of Durres and Bulgaria's Black Sea port of Varna. Albania, Bulgaria, Turkey, Macedonia, Greece and Italy discussed ways of improving transportation in the region while exploring other areas of co-operation. Italy attended as holder of the EU presidency during the next six months, when the project is expected to get off the ground. (ATA, Albanian News, BBC - 30/06/03)
